claim.claim-text:
7. A computer system comprising:
a processor; and
computer readable storage medium accessible to the processor, the storage medium including processor executable instructions that, when executed by the processor, cause the processor to perform operations including:
determining an average maximum bit rate and an average current bit rate for a group of network clients associated with a network node, wherein a determined bit rate is associated with network traffic between the network node and a central office of a network provider;
responsive to a ratio of the average current bit rate to the average maximum bit rate being less than about fifty percent (50%), designating the network node as a degraded node, subjecting the degraded node to enhanced surveillance, and increasing a mitigation priority for the network node;
determining line characteristics for individual network clients coupled to the degraded node; and
performing, for the degraded node, a network operation selected from: triggering additional measurements, broadcasting an alarm over the network, initiating a service call, performing a network diagnostic, and assessing physical network connections;

wherein the network is a multimedia content distribution network.
